data.summary: NJIT CPE Six Sigma and Project Management Training
data.description:
PMP/CAPM Exam Preparation "Boot Camp"
Description
This is an intensive course that will cover all 9 Knowledge Areas covered on the  PMP exam and will highlight important terms and concepts that are "need  to knows."  Students will also learn strategies for preparing for the e xam and for answering exam questions.  A pre-test will be conducted in-c lass for each student to establish their own personal level of knowledge .  At the end of each module on a Knowledge Area\, students will take a  practice test and answers will be reviewed.  At the end of the 5-days\,  students will take a simulated comprehensive practice test covering all  Knowledge Areas.

Six Sigma Green Belt
Description
Certified Six Sig ma Green Belt professionals work on process improvement teams using the  DMAIC approach: DEFINE\, MEASURE\, ANALYZE\, IMPROVE\, CONTROL. NJIT's S ix Sigma Green Belt course gives you the knowledge\, skills and experien ce needed to use Six Sigma methods and tools\, and will help you advance  towards Six Sigma Green Belt Certification.  This course is based on th e American Society for Quality (ASQ) Six Sigma Body of Knowledge\, and i s taught by an ASQ Certified Six Sigma Black Belt instructor.

While t his course will prepare students for the ASQ Six Sigma Green Belt exam\,  it is recommended that you visit the ASQ website to make sure you meet  the eligibility requirements to sit for the ASQ CSSGB Exam.

Six Sigma  Project 
This course provides qualified students with the opportunity  to form a team and work with other students\, under the mentorship of an  American Society for Quality Certified Six Sigma Black Belt\, to comple te a real DMAIC (Define- Measure-Analyze-Improve-Control) Project.

Th e team will select\, and complete\, a real world project using a variety  of Lean Six Sigma tools\, which they are already familiar with. The ins tructor will review each LSS tool before the students apply it to the pr oject.  The instructor will guide the students in the application of eac h tool to the project and the integration of tools within the project.   For more information or how to register for these courses please go to h ttp://www.njit.edu/continuing/ 

Students should expect to perform wor k on the project both during and between class sessions.  This course ma y involve one or more field trips to the location where the process bein g improved is located.
